headline: Texas Pacific Land Set to Join S&P 500, Mueller Industries to Join S&P MidCap 400 and Atlas Energy Solutions to Join S&P SmallCap 600
summary: S&P MidCap 400 constituent Texas Pacific Land Corp. (NYSE: TPL) will replace Marathon Oil Corp. (NYSE: MRO) in the S&P 500, S&P SmallCap 600 constituent Mueller Industries Inc. (NYSE: MLI) will replace Texas Pacific Land in the S&P MidCap 400, and Atlas Energy Solutions Inc. (NYSE: AESI) will replace Mueller Industries in the S&P SmallCap 600 effective prior to the opening of trading on Tuesday, November 26. S&P 500 & 100 constituent ConocoPhillips (NYSE: COP) is acquiring Marathon Oil in a deal

headline: S&P Global Market Intelligence's New Outlook Report Shows the Convergence of Public and Private Credit Markets and Expects the Trend to Continue into 2025
summary: S&P Global Market Intelligence has released a report today highlighting the convergence in public and private credit markets. The newly published Public and Private Markets Outlook: Converging on Credit is part of S&P Global Market Intelligence's Big Picture 2025 Outlook Report Series.

headline: S&P Global Market Intelligence's Big Picture M&A Report Examines the Drivers that Can Set the Pace for the Recovery in Dealmaking
summary: S&P Global Market Intelligence has released an analysis examining the key strategic trends and opportunities that are expected to drive the M&A narrative through 2025. The newly published report, M&A Outlook: Bright spots, shadows on dealmaking horizon, is part of S&P Global Market Intelligence's Big Picture 2025 Outlook Report Series.
